This paper deals with the design of networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The problem is formulated as a graph problem, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of graph theory (cs.DM) or computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic aspect of the problem suggests that it could also belong to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that it could also belong to the category of game theory (cs.GT), which often deals with optimization problems.
